---
// PainPoints.astro — for Water Heater Replacement
---
<section id="why-water-heater-replacement-feels-so-hard" class="relative py-16 px-6 text-base-content border-b-0">
	<div class="absolute inset-0 z-0">
		<div class="w-full h-full bg-gradient-to-b from-base-200/0 to-base-300"></div>
	</div>
	<div class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto">
		<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold mb-12 text-center tracking-tight">
			Why Replacing a Water Heater Is More Frustrating Than It Should Be
		</h2>
		<div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
			<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg border border-base-300 relative">
				<div class="absolute top-9.5 left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-secondary rotate-45 -translate-x-2.5 -translate-y-2.5 rounded-sm rounded-tr-none"></div>
				<div class="card-body">
					<h3 class="card-title text-lg font-semibold">Your Water Heater Went Out Suddenly</h3>
					<p class="leading-relaxed">
						It always happens at the worst time — in the middle of winter, right before guests arrive, or after hours when no one picks up the phone. You want hot water back fast without calling a dozen companies just to get a price.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg border border-base-300 relative">
				<div class="absolute top-9.5 left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-secondary rotate-45 -translate-x-2.5 -translate-y-2.5 rounded-sm rounded-tr-none"></div>
				<div class="card-body">
					<h3 class="card-title text-lg font-semibold">You're Not Sure Who to Trust</h3>
					<p class="leading-relaxed">
						Between big box stores, plumbers, and random online ads, it’s hard to know who’s legit. You don’t want to overpay, but you also don’t want to cut corners or deal with a call-back later.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg border border-base-300 relative">
				<div class="absolute top-9.5 left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-secondary rotate-45 -translate-x-2.5 -translate-y-2.5 rounded-sm rounded-tr-none"></div>
				<div class="card-body">
					<h3 class="card-title text-lg font-semibold">Quotes Are Confusing or Incomplete</h3>
					<p class="leading-relaxed">
						Some companies won’t give you a price until they show up, others don’t explain the full install process. You just want to understand what’s included, what it costs, and when it can be done.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg border border-base-300 relative">
				<div class="absolute top-9.5 left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-secondary rotate-45 -translate-x-2.5 -translate-y-2.5 rounded-sm rounded-tr-none"></div>
				<div class="card-body">
					<h3 class="card-title text-lg font-semibold">You’re Worried About Permits or Code</h3>
					<p class="leading-relaxed">
						You’ve heard horror stories about bad installs, failed inspections, or voided warranties. You want the job done right — by someone who pulls permits and knows local code.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg border border-base-300 relative">
				<div class="absolute top-9.5 left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-secondary rotate-45 -translate-x-2.5 -translate-y-2.5 rounded-sm rounded-tr-none"></div>
				<div class="card-body">
					<h3 class="card-title text-lg font-semibold">You Don't Want a Sales Pitch</h3>
					<p class="leading-relaxed">
						You're not looking for an upsell to tankless, a water softener package, or a maintenance plan. You just want a reliable replacement done right the first time — without the pressure.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg border border-base-300 relative">
				<div class="absolute top-9.5 left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-secondary rotate-45 -translate-x-2.5 -translate-y-2.5 rounded-sm rounded-tr-none"></div>
				<div class="card-body">
					<h3 class="card-title text-lg font-semibold">You're Tired of Getting the Runaround</h3>
					<p class="leading-relaxed">
						You’ve called around and left messages. No call back. Or someone says they’ll come “sometime next week.” You just want someone who will answer, show up, and get the job done.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
